remarks.format:
## Remarks

`HBColor` represents a HarfBuzz color value (`hb_color_t`) as a packed 32-bit unsigned integer
with BGRA byte ordering: `0xBBGGRRAA` (blue in the high byte, alpha in the low byte). This
differs from <xref:SkiaSharp.SKColor>, which uses ARGB ordering (`0xAARRGGBB`).

Use the named properties (<xref:HarfBuzzSharp.HBColor.Red>, <xref:HarfBuzzSharp.HBColor.Green>,
<xref:HarfBuzzSharp.HBColor.Blue>, <xref:HarfBuzzSharp.HBColor.Alpha>) rather than bit-shifting
the raw value, to avoid confusion caused by the non-standard channel order.

`HBColor` is a value type and does not require disposal.

## Examples

```csharp
// Create from individual RGBA components
var color = new HBColor(red: 255, green: 128, blue: 0, alpha: 255);

// Access individual channels
byte r = color.Red;   // 255
byte g = color.Green; // 128
byte b = color.Blue;  // 0
byte a = color.Alpha; // 255

// Convert from/to SKColor using extension methods
SKColor skColor = SKColors.CornflowerBlue;
HBColor hbColor = skColor.ToHBColor();
SKColor back = hbColor.ToSKColor();
```
